# No AI commit attribution

Never add any of the following to git commits, pull requests, code comments, or generated docs:

- `Co-authored-by:` trailers naming Cursor, Claude, Grok, Copilot, Composer, or any other AI product or model
- `Made-with:` / `Made with` trailers naming those products
- `--trailer` flags that inject AI attribution

Commit messages should contain only the subject and body you write for the change. If a hook or environment still injects an AI trailer, strip it before finishing (rewrite the commit without the trailer) rather than leaving it in history.
